com.catchoom.api
Interface CatchoomResponseHandler

public interface CatchoomResponseHandler

CatchoomResponseHanlder expose the interface used by the Catchoom requests to perform callbacks once they have finished. Any class implementing this interface must override its methods. Remember to set the handler to your Catchoom object through setResponseHandler.

Author:
Catchoom

Parameters:

requestFailedResponse

void requestFailedResponse(CatchoomErrorResponseItem responseError)
Callback triggered once a request has completed unsuccessfully. Connection unavailable or server not reached are also considered as unsuccessful requests.

Parameters:
responseError - Catchoom error item containing the HTTP error code and phrase and an error description.
